{{Orphan|date=February 2017}}
'''Robert Levy''' or '''Robert Lévy''' (9 January 1928, in [[Edesheim]] &ndash; 1944) was a French Jewish [[physician]] who served with the German army in [[World War I]], for two years. During [[World War II]], he served as the prisoner-doctor at [[Auschwitz]].<ref name="Priemel/Stiller">Kim Christian Priemel, Alexa Stiller (2012), ''Reassessing the Nuremberg Military Tribunals: Transitional Justice, Trial Narratives, and Historiography.'' Berghahn Books, p. 93. "The prisoner doctor, Robert Levy,<sup>[91]</sup> gave evidence about experimental operations in Auschwitz. He was a French citizen but had served with the German army in World War I for two years..." ''(see)'' "... most of the patients were very unhappy and psychologically broken by the serialization." [https://books.google.com/books?id=76UK3SnMn2cC&lpg=PA93&dq=...%20most%20of%20the%20patients%20were%20very%20unhappy%20and%20psychologically%20broken&pg=PA93#v=onepage&q=...%20most%20of%20the%20patients%20were%20very%20unhappy%20and%20psychologically%20broken&f=false (Google Books preview)]</ref><ref>Endstation Auschwitz: Die Deportation deutscher und österreichischer jüdischer Kinder aus Frankreich. Ein Erinnerungsbuch - Beate Klarsfeld, Serge Klarsfeld - 2008 Page 87 " Beate Klarsfeld, Serge Klarsfeld. Robert Levy kam am 9. Januar 1928 in Edesheim zur Welt. Er wurde in St. Die im Departement Vosges in ..."</ref>
Robert Levy, was arrested on May 12, 1943, in Limoges and deported from Drancy on September 2, 1943, then deported to Auschwitz in 1944 and belonged to the [[concentration camp]] personnel conducting medical treatments at the [[Auschwitz II Birkenau]] [[death factory]]. He worked in the surgical block where the records were also kept. In his notes presented at the [[Nuremberg Trials]] (''SS im Einsatz'', 167/2),<ref name="Schoenberner">{{cite web | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-vW7cG2xi4wC&pg=PA284&lpg=PA284&dq=SS-+Dr+Robert+Levy&source=bl&ots=RDQ-0XvAhr&sig=OdGd_9LvPcFV6VI7jaItq14q3_Q&hl=en&sa=X&ei=HS6kUbXcAoWvigKBkIHQCQ&ved=0CFEQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=SS-%20Dr%20Robert%20Levy&f=false | title=Sources | publisher=Fordham Univ Press | work=The Yellow Star: The Persecutions of the Jews in Europe, 1933-1945 | year=2004 | accessdate=2013-05-27 | author=Gerhard Schoenberner | pages=284 | isbn=0823223906 | format=Google Books}}</ref> Lévy mentioned "losing" 96% of his patients on several different occasions. Every now and then, new selections among prisoners made to strip naked, were arranged on the block by head-doctor [[Friedrich Entress]] (see [[Mauthausen-Gusen camp trials]]). The injured – who were unable to return to work considerably quickly – were sent right away for the so-called "special handling" (''Sonderbehandlung'') at Block 20, which meant one thing: the phenol injection. Lévy seriously believed that he was actually performing medicine, that's why his notes were meticulous.<ref name="Lifton">{{cite web | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bv8IAqVh8EAC&pg=PA189&lpg=PA189&dq=Robert+Levy+SS-&source=bl&ots=-DrPujqXos&sig=Aa2UKxOQ8ScehSy9GXsCIOnG4SQ&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ZyqkUYeSIue9iwLY6YHgBA&ved=0CDIQ6AEwATgK#v=onepage&q=Robert%20Levy%20SS-&f=false | title=Selections in the Camp | publisher=Basic Books | work=The Nazi doctors: medical killing and the psychology of genocide | year=2000 | accessdate=2013-05-27 | author=Robert Lay Lifton | pages=189&ndash;182 | isbn=0465049052 | format=Google Books}}</ref>
Lévy was one of the estimated 6,000 to 8,000 staff members thought to have been involved in the operation of the camp.<ref name="Wittmann">{{cite web | url=http://www.hup.harvard.edu/catalog.php?isbn=9780674063877 | title=Beyond Justice: the Auschwitz Trial | publisher=Harvard University Press | year=2005 | accessdate=2013-05-28 | author=Rebecca Wittmann}}</ref> According to deposition filed after World War II by his second cousin at [[Yad Vashem]] (providing that it was the same person), Lévy was born in Ensisheim, France in 1928 to Georgette and Sylvain Levy and he perished in 1944 while at Auschwitz.<ref name="YV">{{cite web | url=http://db.yadvashem.org/names/nameDetails.html?itemId=935012&language=en | title=Robert Levy | publisher=Yad Vashem The Holocaust Martyrs' and Heroes' Remembrance Authority | work=Central Database | year=2013 | accessdate=2013-05-28 | author=YV}}</ref><ref>The destruction of the European Jews - Page 607 Raul Hilberg - 1973 Affidavit by Dr. Robert Levy (survivor), November 19, 1946, NO-884. wanted to fortify the mass destructive aim with an ..."</ref>
