'''Serfiraz Hanım''' ({{lang-ota|سرفراز خانم}}; {{circa}} 1837 – 9 June 1905) was the sixteenth wife of Sultan [[Abdulmejid I]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]].

==Early life==
Serfiraz Hanım was born in 1837 in [[Abkhazia]]. Born as Ayşe Liah, she was a member of the [[Abkhaz people|Abkhazian]] princely family, Liah. Her father was Prince Osman Bey Liah and her mother was Zeliha Hanım Tapsın.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=71}} She had two sisters, Princess Hüsnümah Hanım and Princess Agâh Hanım.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=72}}

Ayşe had been brought to Istanbul, where her father entrusted her to the imperial harem, where her name according to the custom of the Ottoman court was changed to Serfiraz.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=71}}

==Marriage==
Serfiraz married Abdulmejid in 1851.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=71}} She was given the title of "Altıncı Ikbal". On 9 June 1852, a year after the marriage, she gave birth to her first child, a son, Şehzade Osman Seyfeddin in the Old Çırağan Palace. He died at the age of three.{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=214, n. 30}} She was then given the title of "Beşinci Ikbal", and in 1853, she was given the title of "Dördüncü Ikbal".{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=212 n. 24}} She was then given the title of Üçüncü Ikbal, and in 1855,{{sfn|Sakaoğlu|2008|p=595}} the title of "Ikinci Ikbal". In 1857, she gave birth to her second child, a daughter, Bedia Sultan, who died a month old.{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=214, 231}} Two years later, on 25 July 1860, she gave birth to her third child, a son, Şehzade Selim Süleyman.{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=214}}

Serfiraz Hanım was Abdulmejid's favourite wife. He had alocated her to Yıldız Mansion.{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=213}}

==Later years==
After Abdulmejid's death on 25 June 1861, Serfiraz and her a year old son, Şehzade Süleyman, settled in a mansion located in Ortaköy.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=72}}{{sfn|Sakaoğlu|2008|p=598}}

In the year of 1885 the Sultan's sisters, daughters and wives are said to have incurred a debt of 288,000 purses, approximately 1.15 million pounds sterling, of which, Serfiraz alone was responsible for 125,000 purses, approximately 500,000 pounds sterling.<ref>{{cite book|first=Candan|last=Badem|title=The” Ottoman Crimean War: (1853 - 1856)|publisher=BRILL|year=2010|pages=300|isbn=978-9-004-18205-9}}</ref> 

In March 1898, Serfiraz attended the wedding of Naime Sultan, the daughter of Sultan Abdul Hamid II and Kemaleddin Pasha, the son of Ghazi Osman Pasha.{{sfn|Brookes|2010|p=160, 285}}

[[Hamide Ayşe Sultan]], daughter of Abdul hamid  II, notes in her memoirs that during her father's reign, Serfiraz would attend Ramadan celebrations, and would always sit next to [[Perestu Kadın]].{{sfn|Brookes|2010|p=185}}

==Death==
Serfiraz Hanım settled with her son in his Bebek Palace,{{sfn|Sakaoğlu|2008|p=599}} where she died on 9 June 1905. She was buried in the mausoleum of Şehzade Ahmed Kemaleddin in Yahya Efendi Cemetery, [[Istanbul]].{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=73}}{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=214}}{{sfn|Brookes|2010|p=290}}

